// ---- library expansion v8 · the missing rungs ------------------------------
// The audit found the library's holes are not exotic — they are all on the BOTTOM
// rungs. It was written by someone who already knows how to train. Every exercise
// below fills a structural gap, and each one says which.
//
// The two worst holes it closes:
//   · There was no rung between the row and the first pull-up, so the library's advice
//     was "do negatives" — the highest eccentric load you can produce, aimed at the
//     least adapted tissue you own. Tendon adapts in 8–12 weeks; muscle in 2–3. That
//     is how calisthenics elbows get destroyed, and it is the most common advice online.
//   · The hinge went from a glute bridge (L1) straight to the Nordic curl (L3) — which
//     means the single strongest injury-prevention finding in the literature (eccentric
//     hamstring work, −57 to −70 % of hamstring injuries) was gated behind an advanced
//     exercise. It cannot be.
